│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The crash occurs when `CleanupReturnInst::getCleanupPad()` tries to cast its first operand to a `CleanupPadInst`, but the operand is actually a `PoisonValue` (token poison). This happens because during CFG  │
│ simplification, some cleanuppad instructions are replaced with poison values when their blocks are being deleted, but the corresponding cleanupret instructions still reference these poison values.           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log:                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The debug log shows that several blocks are being removed as dead code:                                                                                                                                        │
│ - `panic1` (invoke block)                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ - `funclet_bb14` (cleanuppad block)                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ - `unreachable` (unreachable block)                                                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ After these removals, there's a cleanupret instruction in `bb13` that references `%cleanuppad`, but this cleanuppad was in the now-deleted `funclet_bb14` block. The cleanuppad gets replaced with poison, but │
│ the cleanupret still exists and tries to access it.                                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Looking at the `simplifyCleanupReturn` function in `SimplifyCFG.cpp`, there's already a check for `UndefValue` operands on line 5526, with a comment explaining that "It is possible to transiantly have an    │
│ undef cleanuppad operand because we have deleted some, but not all, dead blocks." However, the code doesn't check for `PoisonValue` operands, which can also occur during dead block elimination.              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ In the debugger, we confirmed that the problematic `CleanupReturnInst` has a `token poison` operand instead of a valid `CleanupPadInst`. The existing check only handles `UndefValue` but not `PoisonValue`,   │
│ causing the cast assertion to fail.                                                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The fix is to extend the existing check in `simplifyCleanupReturn` to also handle `PoisonValue` operands, similar to how it already handles `UndefValue`. This should be done at line 5526 in                  │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyCFG.cpp`.                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ By adding a check for `PoisonValue` alongside the existing `UndefValue` check, we prevent the invalid cast that causes the assertion failure. This allows the pass to safely skip processing cleanupret        │
│ instructions that reference dead cleanuppad instructions, which will eventually be cleaned up by dead block elimination.                                                                                       │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
